126 A.3d 71 Michael Davon CHRISTIAN v. Stewart LEVITAS. No. 70,

Sept. Term, 2015.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Nov. 23, 2015. Brian S. Brown (Saul E. Kerpelman, Saul E. Kerpelman & Associates, Baltimore, MD), for Petitioner. William C. Parler, Jr. (Kelly A. Grafton, Parler & Wobber, L.L.P., Towson, MD), for Respondent.

Submitted before: BARBERA, C.J., BATTAGLIA, GREENE, ADKINS, McDONALD, WATTS, JJ.

PER CURIAM

ORDER.

The Court having considered and granted the petition for a writ of certiorari in the above entitled case, it is this 23rd day of November, 2015,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that the judgment of the Court of Special Appeals be, and it is hereby, *241vacated and the case is remanded to that Court for further reconsideration in light of Jakeem Roy v. Sandra B. Dackman et al., 445 Md. 23, 124 A.3d 169 (2015). Costs in this Court to be paid by the Respondent, and costs in the Court of Special Appeals to abide the result.
